<subSubSection id="6D837C851034FFABDBB2FDB049372D58" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="description">
<paragraph id="25262F0E1034FFABDBB2FDB04D642838" blockId="17.[151,460,726,789]" box="[151,337,763,789]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
(
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDBBAFDB04CC32838" box="[159,246,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Asianthrips species. (1) A. balianus, female (mac). (2) A. bamboosielloides, female (mac). A. bicolor, 3–4; (3) Female (mac); (4) Female (mic). (5) A. borneoensis, female (mac). A. dasycornis, 6–7; (6) Female (mac); (7) Male (mic). A. denticornis, 8–9; (8) Male (mac); (9) Female (mic). (10) A. longior, female (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404866/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDA27FDB04D7C2838" box="[258,329,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">72–79</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1034FFABDBB2FC0849192EEC" blockId="17.[151,1437,835,1941]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1034FFABDBB2FC084D4D2871" box="[151,376,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. 
<materialsCitation id="95F125531034FFABDAACFC08491D2EEC" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3744622311" collectionCode="III, VII, VIII, IV, V, VI" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" specimenCount="5" typeStatus="holotype">
Body dark brown (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABD942FC084E8B2870" box="[615,702,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Asianthrips species. (1) A. balianus, female (mac). (2) A. bamboosielloides, female (mac). A. bicolor, 3–4; (3) Female (mac); (4) Female (mic). (5) A. borneoensis, female (mac). A. dasycornis, 6–7; (6) Female (mac); (7) Male (mic). A. denticornis, 8–9; (8) Male (mac); (9) Female (mic). (10) A. longior, female (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404866/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Antennal segment 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABD88BFC084FFF2870" box="[942,970,835,861]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">III</collectionCode>
yellowish, shaded with brown at apical half; the remaining segments dark brown. All femora dark brown; fore tibiae yellowish, shaded with pale brown, mid and hind tibiae brown with bases and apices yellowish; tarsi yellow. Fore wings weakly shaded with brown. Body setae almost colourless. Head longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABD9D1FCE44F7228E4" box="[756,839,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
), about 1.14 times as long as wide in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1034FFABDFCDFCE4497B28E4" box="[1256,1358,943,969]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">holotype</typeStatus>
; dorsal surface generally sculptured with transverse reticulation, but ocellar triangle with polygonal reticulation. Cheeks very weakly rounded, very weakly narrowed toward base. Postocular setae a little longer than eyes. Postocellar setae almost as long as a diameter of posterior ocellus, or a little longer. Eyes 0.34–0.36 times as long as head in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1034FFABDE16FB5049AC2F18" box="[1331,1433,1051,1077]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">holotype</typeStatus>
. Antennal segments 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABDA52FB744DAB2F74" box="[375,414,1087,1113]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">VII</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABDAFDFB744E3D2F74" box="[472,520,1087,1113]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">VIII</collectionCode>
somewhat broadly fused, but 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABD846FB744FA62F74" box="[867,915,1087,1113]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">VIII</collectionCode>
not constricted basally (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDF8BFB7449362F74" box="[1198,1283,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
); segment 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABDEA5FB7449A92F74" box="[1408,1436,1087,1113]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">III</collectionCode>
with three sense cones; segment 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABD931FB284E042F50" box="[532,561,1123,1149]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">IV</collectionCode>
the largest, with a series of 18–19 short and stout setae on ventral surface, segments 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABDA2DFBCC4D292F8C" box="[264,284,1159,1185]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABDA70FBCC4D462F8C" box="[341,371,1159,1185]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">VI</collectionCode>
each with 11–13 and 6–8 same setae (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABD814FBCC4FB32F8C" box="[817,902,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
), respectively. Maxillary stylets long, reaching compound eyes, rather close together, closer than 1/4 of the head width apart at the basal collar of head. Pronotum almost smooth, about 0.6 times as long as head and 2.03 times as wide as long in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1034FFABDF66FB84489C2FC4" box="[1091,1193,1231,1257]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">holotype</typeStatus>
; epim the longest, pa 0.59–0.62 times as long as median length of pronotum. Metanotum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABD891FBB8483D2E20" box="[948,1032,1266,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
) polygonally reticulated anteriorly, longitudinally reticulated posteriorly. Mesopresternum and mesoeusternum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDF20FA5C486F2E1F" box="[1029,1114,1303,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
) narrowly fused, somewhat long sutures between them at both sides. Fore tarsus unarmed. Fore wings with 4–6 duplicated cilia, 5– 
<quantity id="E26182EB1034FFABDE20FA71491B2E78" box="[1285,1326,1338,1365]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1034FFABDE16FA7049AC2E78" box="[1331,1433,1339,1365]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">holotype</typeStatus>
. Pelta trapezoid (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDA69FA144D952E54" box="[332,416,1374,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
). Tergites normal (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABD94AFA144EF72E54" box="[623,706,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
), tergites 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABD80BFA144F7F2E54" box="[814,842,1375,1401]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">III</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1034FFABD87DFA144F592E54" box="[856,876,1375,1401]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
much wider than pronotum. S1 setae on tergite IX weakly expanded, about 0.8 times as long as tube, S2 blunt or very weakly expanded, a little shorter than S1. Tube (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDB85FAEC4CC42EEC" box="[160,241,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
) 0.55 times as long as head in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1034FFABD96FFAEC4E852EEC" box="[586,688,1447,1473]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">holotype</typeStatus>
. Anal setae almost as long as or a little shorter than tube
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1034FFABDBE2FA8049372D58" blockId="17.[151,1437,835,1941]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1034FFABDBE2FA804D432EC8" bold="true" box="[199,374,1483,1509]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Measurements</emphasis>
. Female 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1034FFABDAC0FA804E722EC8" box="[485,583,1483,1509]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">holotype</typeStatus>
(mac.) in microns. Distended body length 1950. Head length 183, width across cheeks 161. Compound eye dorsal length 63–65. Pronotum length 110, width 223. Fore wing length about 820. Tube length 100, width across base 54. Antenna length about 400, segments III–VIII length (width) as follows: 61 (34), 67 (35), 53 (28), 50 (25), 47 (21), 33 (13). Postocular setae 70–73. Pronotal aa 48–50, am 48–50, ml 56–60, pa 65–68, epim 75–78. S1 setae on tergite IX 79–82, S2 setae on tergite IX 74–78. Anal setae 95–96.
</paragraph>
