<subSubSection id="6D837C851034FFABDBE2F98C4D852CB8" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25262F0E1034FFABDBE2F98C4D852CB8" blockId="17.[151,1437,835,1941]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1034FFABDBE2F98C4D012DCC" bold="true" box="[199,308,1735,1761]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1034FFABDA66F98C4D802DCC" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[323,437,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longior">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1034FFABDA66F98C4D802DCC" box="[323,437,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">A. longior</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is slightly similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1034FFABD982F98C4F752DCC" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[679,832,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasycornis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1034FFABD982F98C4F752DCC" box="[679,832,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">A. dasycornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having brown body and a series of short and stout setae on the ventral surface of intermediate antennal segments at least in the macropterous female (cf. 
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDE1FF9A049A52C28" box="[1338,1424,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1034FFABDA28F8444DB52C04" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[269,384,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longior">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1034FFABDA28F8444DB52C04" box="[269,384,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">A. longior</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the maxillary stylets long and rather close and retracted to the posterior margins of the compound eyes (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDA7DF8784D982C60" box="[344,429,1843,1869]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
), also the mesopresternum and mesoeusternum are narrowly fused (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDF97F878493D2C63" box="[1202,1288,1843,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–79" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1569,1593]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[157,1430,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 72–79. Asianthrips longior, sp. n., female (mac). (72) Head.Antennal segments III–VIII, 73–74; (73) Dorsal aspect; (74) Ventral aspect; (75) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (76) Ferna–mesopresternum; (77) Fore wing; (78) Tergite IV; (79) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404898/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
). In contrast, 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1034FFABDBB2F81C4D052C5C" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,304,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasycornis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1034FFABDBB2F81C4D052C5C" box="[151,304,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">A. dasycornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short and rather wide maxillary stylets (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABD80FF81C4FFE2C5C" box="[810,971,1878,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 55–61" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,181,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-29@14.[158,1430,181,1753]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 55–61. Asianthrips dasycornis, sp. n., female. (55) Head–tergite II (mac); (56) Head– tergite (mic); (57) Antenna, dorsal aspect (mac); (58) Antenna, ventral aspect (mac); (59) Ferna–mesopresternum (mac); (60) Tergite IV (mic); (61) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404892/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Figs. 55 &amp; 56</figureCitation>
), and broadly fused mesopresternum and mesoeusternum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1034FFABDA73F8314D912CB8" box="[342,420,1914,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 55–61" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,181,1752]" captionTargetId="figure-29@14.[158,1430,181,1753]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 55–61. Asianthrips dasycornis, sp. n., female. (55) Head–tergite II (mac); (56) Head– tergite (mic); (57) Antenna, dorsal aspect (mac); (58) Antenna, ventral aspect (mac); (59) Ferna–mesopresternum (mac); (60) Tergite IV (mic); (61) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404892/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Fig.59</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
